'''Karim Boudiaf''' ({{langx|ar|كريم بوضياف}}; born 16 September 1990) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Al-Duhail SC|Al-Duhail]] in the [[Qatar Stars League]]. He can play as a [[defender (association football)|central defender]] and as a [[defensive midfielder]]. Born in France, he represents the [[Qatar national football team|Qatar national team]].

==Club career==
On 5 September 2010, Boudiaf started for [[Lekhwiya SC|Lekhwiya]] in the final of the [[2010 Sheikh Jassem Cup]] against [[Al-Arabi SC (Qatar)|Al-Arabi Sports Club]].<ref>[http://www.alarab.com.qa/details.php?docId=147618&issueNo=994&secId=20 رأس «كابوري» تمنح العربي كأس الشيخ جاسم] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110903151756/http://www.alarab.com.qa/details.php?docId=147618&issueNo=994&secId=20 |date=3 September 2011 }}</ref>

==International career==
Boudiaf was born in France, and is of Moroccan-Algerian descent. On 22 December 2009, Boudiaf was called up to the [[Algeria Olympic football team|Algeria U23 national team]] for a training camp in [[Algiers]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dzfoot.com/news-5493/en-espoirs-27-joueurs-convoques/ |title=EN Espoirs : 27 joueurs convoqués |access-date=6 September 2010 |archive-date=11 September 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120911132252/http://www.dzfoot.com/news-5493/en-espoirs-27-joueurs-convoques/ |url-status=dead }}</ref>

Boudiaf acquired Qatari nationality and was called up to the [[Qatar national football team|Qatar national team]] on 13 November 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.dzfoot.com/2013/11/qatar-calls-up-algerian-duo-of-boualem-khoukhi-and-karim-boudiaf/ |title=Qatar calls up Algerian duo of Boualem Khoukhi and Karim Boudiaf |publisher=dzfoot.com |date=13 November 2013 |access-date=30 December 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131230233723/http://en.dzfoot.com/2013/11/qatar-calls-up-algerian-duo-of-boualem-khoukhi-and-karim-boudiaf/ |archive-date=30 December 2013 }}</ref> He was capped in an unofficial friendly exhibition match against Saudi club [[Al-Hilal FC|Al Hilal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.qfa.com.qa/al-hilal-of-ksa-hold-qatar-reserves-to-goalless-draw/|title=Al Hilal of KSA hold Qatar reserves to goalless draw|work=Qatar Football Association |date=20 November 2013 |publisher=qfa.com.qa|access-date=30 December 2013}}</ref> He made his official debut for the team on 25 December in the 2014 WAFF Championship in a 1–0 win against [[Palestine national football team|Palestine]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.the-waff.com/assets/reports/391_match.pdf|title=Match report|publisher=the-waff.com|access-date=30 December 2013|archive-date=27 December 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131227012543/http://www.the-waff.com/assets/reports/391_match.pdf|url-status=dead}}</ref> Boudiaf's first goal came fifteen caps in. He cancelled out a [[Stuart Dallas]] goal as Qatar drew with [[Northern Ireland national football team|Northern Ireland]] in England.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/may/31/qatar-northern-ireland-friendly-crewe-fifa-gresty-road|title=Qatar try to shift focus back on football with Northern Ireland draw|work=The Guardian|date=31 May 2015|access-date=26 June 2015}}</ref>

